t, Grant F. (1994). ''The Sculpted Word: Keats, Ekphrasis, and the Visual Arts''. Hanover, NH: University Press of New England. {{ISBN|0-87451-679-X}}\n*Stillinger, Jack (1982). ''Complete Poems''. Cambridge, Massachusetts: Belknap Press of Harvard University Press. {{ISBN|0-674-15430-4}}\n*Strachan, John (Ed.) (2003). ''A Routledge Literary Sourcebook on the Poems of John Keats''. New York: Routledge. {{ISBN|0-415-23478-6}}\n*[[Helen Vendler|Vendler, Helen]] (1983). ''The Odes of John Keats''. Belknap Press {{ISBN|0-674-63076-9}}\n*Walsh, John Evangelist (1999). ''Darkling I Listen: The Last Days and Death of John Keats''. New York: St. Martin's Press.\n*Walsh, William (1957). \"John Keats\", in ''From Blake to Byron''. Middlesex: Penguin.\n*Ward, Aileen (1963). ''John Keats: The Making of a Poet''. London: Secker & Warburg.\n*Wolfson, Susan J. (1986). ''The Questioning Presence''. Ithaca, New York: Cornell University Press. {{ISBN|0-8014-1909-3}}\n{{refend}}\n\n==Further reading==\n* Bate, Walter Jackson. ''Negative Capability: The Intuitive Approach in Keats''. New York: Contra Mundum Press, 2012.\n* Cox, Jeffrey N. ''Poetry and Politics in the Cockney School: Keats, Shelley, Hunt and Their Circle''. Cambridge: Cambridge University Press, 2004. {{ISBN|978-0521604239}}\n*Kirkland, John (2008). ''[[Love Letters of Great Men]], Vol. 1''. CreateSpace Publishing.\n*Kottoor, Gopikrishnan (1994). ''The Mask of Death: The Final Days of John Keats, (A Radio Play)''. Writers WorkShop Kolkata, 1994.\n*[[Amy Lowell|Lowell, Amy]] (1925). ''John Keats''. 2 vols. Boston: Houghton Mifflin.\n*Parson, Donald (1954). ''Portraits of Keats''. Cleveland: World Publishing Co.\n*Plumly, Stanley (2008). ''Posthumous Keats''. New York: W.W. Norton & Co.\n*[[Joanna Richardson|Richardson, Joanna]] (1963). ''The Everlasting Spell. A Study of Keats and His Friends''. London: Cape\n*Richardson, Joanna (1980). ''Keats and His Circle. An Album of Portraits''. London: Cassell.\n*[[William Michael Rossetti|Rossetti, William Michael]] (1887). ''The Life and Writings of John Keats''. London: Walter Scott.\n*[[Richard Marggraf Turley|Turley, Richard Marggraf]] (2004). ''Keats' Boyish Imagination''. London: Routledge, {{ISBN|978-0-415-28882-8}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Portal|Poetry}}\n{{commons category|John Keats}}\n{{wikiquote}}\n{{Wikisource author}}\n* [http://www.bl.uk/people/john-keats John Keats] on the British Library's Discovering Literature website\n* [https://www.poetryfoundation.org/poets/john-keats John Keats] at the [[Poetry Foundation]]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20140403135411/http://www.poets.org/poet.php/prmPID/66 Biography of Keats at poets.org]\n* {{Gutenberg author |id=Keats,+John | name=John Keats}}\n* {{Internet Archive author |sname=John Keats}}\n* {{Librivox author |id=330}}\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20170104234150/http://hcl.harvard.edu/libraries/houghton/collections/modern/keats.cfm The Harvard Keats Collection] at the [[Houghton Library]], Harvard University\n* [http://www.bl.uk/onlinegallery/features/keats/keats.html John Keats] at the [[British Library]]\n* [https://www.cityoflondon.gov.uk/things-to-do/keats-house/Pages/default.aspx Keats House, Hampstead: official website]\n* [http://keats-shelley-house.org The Keats-Shelley House museum in Rome]\n* [http://www.npg.org.uk/live/search/person.asp?search=ss&sText=Keats&LinkID=mp02480 John Keats] at the [[National Portrait Gallery, London]]\n* [http://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/nra/searches/subjectView.asp?ID=P15963 Keats, John (1795\u20131821) Poet] at the [[National Register of Archives]]\n\n{{John Keats}}\n{{Romanticism}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Keats, John}}\n[[Category:1795 births]]\n[[Category:1821 deaths]]\n[[Category:19th-century English writers]]\n[[Category:19th-century poets]]\n[[Category:Alumni of King's College London]]\n[[Category:Burials in the Protestant Cemetery, Rome]]\n[[Category:19th-century deaths from tuberculosis]]\n[[Category:Epic 